Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{240%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @dried cranberries{30%g}, then bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a lid on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed) and @parsnip{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}(peeled), then cut each half into 4-6 wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @harissa paste{50%g}, half the @honey{30%g} and the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then set aside.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 minute.

Pop the carrot, parsnip and onion onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @olive oil{for roasting} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When the veg has ~{5%minutes} remaining, remove the tray from the oven and drizzle over the remaining honey.

Return to the oven and bake for the remaining time until caramelised, ~{5%minutes}.

Once the bulgur is cooked, stir through the @butter{20%g}. Fluff it up with a #fork{} to separate the grains.

Share the bulgur between your #bowls{} and pile the roasted veg on top. Drizzle over the honey harissa dressing.

Crumble the @goat's cheese{75%g} over the top and scatter with the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!